ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/9627/documentation

Data is based on the environmental report of the two gas processing plants of Norway Karsto and Kollsnes.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]



Drying and processing of 1 m3 natural gas before being inducted in transport network.
category: D:Electricity, gas, steam and air conditioning supply/35:Electricity, gas, steam and air conditioning supply/352:Manufacture of gas; distribution of gaseous fuels through mains/3520:Manufacture of gas; distribution of gaseous fuels through mains

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Data for 2000 is used. Emissions of CO2 and NMVOC were stable in the past 5 years. NOx increased slightly per tonne of product in the  processing plant Karsto.
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: The figures are based on Norwegian data for the gas processing plants Karsto and Kollsnes. A
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Kårstø started operation in 1985 and Kollsnes in 1996. No further information on technology available.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: The figures are based on the data for the Norwegian gas processing plants Karsto and Kollsnes. About 60% of the Norwegian gas is processed either at Kårstø or at Kollsnes. The rest is processed on the platforms. An average of both plants was taken. Kollsnes is the onshore processing plant for the offshore Troll gas field. Part of the processing (mainly water separation) of the Troll gas is performed on the Troll platform, where as the final processing is performed at Kollsnes. The Troll gas contains very little liquids (condensate and oil) compared to the other fields on the Norwegian Shelf. Kårstø is a complex facility. The main energy consumption for processing is for distillation, i.e. heating of the gas to distill off its various components. The emissions of flared gas and of use of fuel gas are included in the process. The Norwegian data can be extrapolated for European processing of gas
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Data is based on environmental report. No information about the sampling procedure.
